(46, 1, '2016-02-09 18:41:15', '2016-02-09 12:41:15', '<p style="text-align: justify;"><span style="color: #800000;"><b>Rangpur Division</b></span> (Bengali: <span style="color: #800000;"><strong><span lang="bn">রংপুর বিভাগ</span></strong></span>) was formed on 25 January 2010, as <span style="color: #800000;"><strong>Bangladesh</strong></span>''s 7th division. Before that, it had been the northern eight districts of the <strong>Rajshahi Division</strong>. The Rangpur division consists of eight districts. There are 58 Upazillas or subdistricts under these eight districts. Rangpur is the northernmost division of Bangladesh and has a population of 15,665,000 at the 2011 Census.</p>\r\nThe <span style="color: #800000;"><strong>08 districts</strong></span> of <strong>Rangpur division</strong> are as follow-\r\n<ol>\r\n<ol>\r\n<ol>\r\n<ol>\r\n<ol>\r\n<ol>\r\n	<li><a href="http://localhost/travelguide/?page_id=653" target="_blank">Rangpur District</a></li>\r\n	<li><a href="http://localhost/travelguide/?page_id=662" target="_blank">Dinajpur</a></li>\r\n	<li><a href="http://localhost/travelguide/?page_id=691" target="_blank">Gaibandha</a></li>\r\n	<li><a href="http://localhost/travelguide/?page_id=669" target="_blank">Kurigram</a></li>\r\n	<li><a href="http://localhost/travelguide/?page_id=694" target="_blank">Lalmonirhat</a></li>\r\n	<li><a href="http://localhost/travelguide/?page_id=678" target="_blank">Nilphamari</a></li>\r\n	<li><a href="http://localhost/travelguide/?page_id=686" target="_blank">Panchagarh</a></li>\r\n	<li><a href="http://localhost/travelguide/?page_id=686" target="_blank">Thakurgaon</a></li>\r\n</ol>\r\n</ol>\r\n</ol>\r\n</ol>\r\n</ol>\r\n</ol>\r\n&nbsp;\r\n\r\n&nbsp;', 'Rangpur Division', '', 'publish', 'closed', 'closed', '', 'rangpur-division', '', '', '2016-02-13 23:54:09', '2016-02-13 17:54:09', '', 0, 'http://localhost/travelguide/?page_id=46', 0, 'page', '', 0),
