(48, 1, '2016-02-09 18:41:40', '2016-02-09 12:41:40', '<p style="text-align: justify;"><span style="color: #800000;"><b>Mymensingh Division</b> </span>(Bengali: <span style="color: #800000;"><strong><span lang="bn" xml:lang="bn">ময়মনসিংহ বিভাগ</span></strong></span>) is one of the <strong>eight administrative divisions</strong> of Bangladesh. It has an area of 10,485 km² and a population of 11,370,000 as of the 2011 census. It was created in 2015 from districts previously comprising the northern part of <strong>Dhaka Division</strong>. Its headquarters are in <strong>Mymensingh</strong> city in <strong>Mymensingh District.</strong></p>\r\n<p style="text-align: justify;">The Greater Mymensingh region (Mymensingh District along with six other neighbouring districts) was created as a Mymensingh district by the British Indian government in 1787. Later, it was reorganized in two phases into four districts-</p>\r\n\r\n<ol>\r\n	<li style="text-align: justify;"><a href="http://localhost/travelguide/?page_id=516" target="_blank">Mymensingh District</a></li>\r\n	<li style="text-align: justify;"><a href="http://localhost/travelguide/?page_id=524" target="_blank">Netrakona</a></li>\r\n	<li style="text-align: justify;"><a href="http://localhost/travelguide/?page_id=537" target="_blank">Jamalpur</a></li>\r\n	<li style="text-align: justify;"><a href="http://localhost/travelguide/?page_id=533" target="_blank">Sherpur</a></li>\r\n</ol>', 'Mymensingh Division', '', 'publish', 'closed', 'closed', '', 'mymensingh-division', '', '', '2016-02-13 19:58:47', '2016-02-13 13:58:47', '', 0, 'http://localhost/travelguide/?page_id=48', 0, 'page', '', 0),
