rong>Dhakeshwari Temple</strong></span></h2>\r\n<img class="wp-image-103 alignleft" src="http://localhost/travelguide/wp-content/uploads/2016/02/dhakeshwari-temple-300x225.jpg" alt="dhakeshwari-temple" width="169" height="127" />\r\n<p style="text-align: justify;">Great place for whom they follow Hindu religion. It is one of the oldest temple is dhaka and there are many myths with this as well. For outsider, obviously a great place to see Hindu culture</p>\r\n\r\n<h2 class="title"><span style="color: #000080;"> </span></h2>\r\n<h2 class="heading_height"></h2>\r\n<h2 class="heading_height"></h2>\r\n<h2 class="heading_height"><span style="color: #000080;"><strong>Bangabandhu Sheikh Mujibur Rahman Novo Theatre</strong></span></h2>\r\n<div class="heading_name_wrapper">\r\n\r\n<img class="wp-image-104 alignleft" src="http://localhost/travelguide/wp-content/uploads/2016/02/novo-theatre-right-side-300x225.jpg" alt="novo-theatre-right-side" width="168" height="126" />\r\n<p style="text-align: justify;"><strong><span style="color: #800000;">The Novo Theatre</span></strong> is situated right in the heart of Dhaka city and it’s a nice place to visit especially if you have kids with you. It’s a planetarium theater . They have a large Dome shaped gallery , where 3D movie is shown. The 3D movie is projected on the large Dome shaped ceiling of the gallery hall.</p>\r\n\r\n</div>\r\n<h2 id="HEADING" class="heading_name "></h2>\r\n<h2 class="heading_name "><span style="color: #000080;"><strong>Dhaka Zoo</strong></span></h2>\r\n<p style="text-align: justify;"><span style="color: #800000;"><strong><img class="wp-image-137 alignleft" src="http://localhost/travelguide/wp-content/uploads/2016/02/index-1.jpg" alt="index" width="169" height="127" />Dhaka Zoo</strong></span> has a huge area with natural beauty. Many varities of animal are there but need to develop more and more. Authorities should make concentration for its development excepts that it is good place to visit. Everyone can visit it.</p>\r\n\r\n<div class="heading_name_wrapper"></div>\r\n<h2 style="text-align: justify;"></h2>\r\n<h2><span style="color: #000080;">Shahid Minar</span></h2>\r\n<div class="heading_name_wrapper">\r\n<p style="text-align: justify;"><img class="wp-image-113 alignleft" src="http://localhost/travelguide/wp-content/uploads/2016/02/shahid-minar-300x200.jpg" alt="shahid-minar" width="169" height="127" />A symbol of the Language Movement. The Monument was built to commemorate the dead after equal status was given. it was designed and built by Hamid Ur Rahman a Bangladeshi sculptor in collaboration with Novera Ahmed. The monument stood until the Bangladesh Liberation War in 1971, when it was demolished completely during Operation Searchlight.</p>\r\n\r\n</div>\r\n<h2 class="heading_name "></h2>\r\n<h2 id="HEADING" class="heading_name "><span style="color: #000080;">Liberation War Museum</span></h2>\r\n<img class="wp-image-96 alignleft" src="http://localhost/travelguide/wp-content/uploads/2016/02/bangladesh-national-museum-1-300x225.jpg" alt="bangladesh-national-museum" width="169" height="127" />\r\n<p style="text-align: justify;">The museum is well kept and well curated if a little cramped. The best place to garner an understanding of the history of the nation, beginning from Bengal''s contribution to the Indian independence movement right down to the birth of Bangladesh. The latter part can be disturbing to say the least. they also have a small bookshop.</p>\r\n\r\n<h2 class="heading_height"></h2>\r\n<h2 style="text-align: justify;"><span style="color: #000080;">National Srity Showudho</span></h2>\r\n<p style="text-align: justify;"><img class="wp-image-112 alignleft" src="http://localhost/travelguide/wp-content/uploads/2016/02/index.jpg" alt="index" width="169" height="127" />It''s distance is about 35 km from Dhaka city at Savar.It built in memory of millions who died in the liberation war in 1971.This 50 m. high and beautifully monument''s structure was designed by the famous architect Mr.Moinul Hossain.In liberation time about 3 million peoples had died so for this memory,Government dicided to build a memorial monument in Savar.</p>\r\n\r\n<h2 class="heading_height"></h2>\r\n<h2 class="heading_height"><span style="color: #000080;"><strong>Ahsan Manzil</strong></span></h2>\r\n<img class="wp-image-98 alignleft" src="http://localhost/travelguide/wp-content/uploads/2016/02/filename-dscn0388-jpg-300x225.jpg" alt="filename-dscn0388-jpg" width="169" height="127" />\r\n<p class="heading_name_wrapper" style="text-align: justify;"><span style="color: #800000;"><strong>Ahsan Manjil</strong></span> is situated at Kumartoli in Dhaka city on the bank of the Buriganga river,it was the residential palace and the Banglow of the Nawabs of Dhaka.Long time it was careless and closed but few years ago it has been turned into a museum. The costraction  of this palace was begun in 1859 completed in 1872.Abdul Gani named it Ahsan Manjil after his son Khawja Ahsanullah.At that time the newly built palace was known as Rang Mahal and earlier one is called Andar Mahal.On April 7,1888,a terible tornedo  caused severe damage to Ahsan Manjil.Particularly the Andar Mahal was fully damaged.Nawab Ahsanullah rebuilt the Rang Mahal and Andar Mahal using good quality breaks from Ranigong.</p>\r\n\r\n<div class="heading_name_wrapper">\r\n<h2 class="heading_name "><span style="color: #000080;"><strong>National Parliament House</strong></span></h2>\r\n<p style="text-align: justify;"><img class=" wp-image-111 alignleft" src="http://localhost/travelguide/wp-content/uploads/2016/02/back-side-from-zia-uddan-300x225.jpg" alt="back-side-from-zia-uddan" width="169" height="127" />One of a nice place to see in Dhaka. This is in central Dhaka. By Bus it will take from Airport to Parliament House not more than 20 Minutes.</p>\r\n\r\n</div>', 'Dhaka District', '', 'inherit', 'closed', 'closed', '', '72-revision-v1', '', '', '2016-02-10 09:45:12', '2016-02-10 03:45:12', '', 72, 'http://localhost/travelguide/index.php/2016/02/10/72-revision-v1/', 0, 'revision', '', 0),
