n<p style="text-align: justify;"><span style="color: #800000;"><strong><img class="wp-image-98 alignleft" src="http://localhost/travelguide/wp-content/uploads/2016/02/filename-dscn0388-jpg-300x225.jpg" alt="filename-dscn0388-jpg" width="169" height="127" />Ahsan Manjil</strong></span> is situated at Kumartoli in Dhaka city on the bank of the Buriganga river,it was the residential palace and the Banglow of the Nawabs of Dhaka.Long time it was careless and closed but few years ago it has been turned into a museum. The costraction  of this palace was begun in 1859 completed in 1872.Abdul Gani named it Ahsan Manjil after his son Khawja Ahsanullah.At that time the newly built palace was known as Rang Mahal and earlier one is called Andar Mahal.On April 7,1888,a terible tornedo  caused severe damage to Ahsan Manjil.Particularly the Andar Mahal was fully damaged.Nawab Ahsanullah rebuilt the Rang Mahal and Andar Mahal using good quality breaks from Ranigong.</p>\r\n&nbsp;\r\n<h2></h2>\r\n<h2><span style="color: #000080;">Shahid Minar</span></h2>\r\n<p style="text-align: justify;"><img class="wp-image-113 alignleft" src="http://localhost/travelguide/wp-content/uploads/2016/02/shahid-minar-300x200.jpg" alt="shahid-minar" width="169" height="127" />A symbol of the Language Movement. The Monument was built to commemorate the dead after equal status was given. it was designed and built by Hamid Ur Rahman a Bangladeshi sculptor in collaboration with Novera Ahmed. The monument stood until the Bangladesh Liberation War in 1971, when it was demolished completely during Operation Searchlight.</p>\r\n\r\n<h2><span style="color: #000080;"><strong>Bangabandhu Sheikh Mujibur Rahman Novo Theatre</strong></span></h2>\r\n<p style="text-align: justify;"><span style="color: #800000;"><strong><img class="wp-image-111 alignleft" src="http://localhost/travelguide/wp-content/uploads/2016/02/back-side-from-zia-uddan-300x225.jpg" alt="back-side-from-zia-uddan" width="169" height="127" />The Novo Theatre</strong> </span>is situated right in the heart of Dhaka city and it’s a nice place to visit especially if you have kids with you. It’s a planetarium theater . They have a large Dome shaped gallery , where 3D movie is shown. The 3D movie is projected on the large Dome shaped ceiling of the gallery hall.</p>\r\n\r\n<h2></h2>\r\n<h2></h2>\r\n&nbsp;\r\n<h2></h2>\r\n<h2></h2>\r\n&nbsp;\r\n\r\n&nbsp;\r\n<div class="heading_name_wrapper">\r\n<h2 class="heading_name "><span style="color: #000080;"><strong>National Parliament House</strong></span></h2>\r\n<p style="text-align: justify;"><img class=" wp-image-111 alignleft" src="http://localhost/travelguide/wp-content/uploads/2016/02/back-side-from-zia-uddan-300x225.jpg" alt="back-side-from-zia-uddan" width="169" height="127" />One of a nice place to see in Dhaka. This is in central Dhaka. By Bus it will take from Airport to Parliament House not more than 20 Minutes.</p>\r\n\r\n</div>\r\n&nbsp;\r\n<h2></h2>\r\n<h2><span style="color: #000080;"><strong> </strong></span></h2>\r\n&nbsp;\r\n<h2></h2>\r\n&nbsp;', 'Dhaka District', '', 'inherit', 'closed', 'closed', '', '72-revision-v1', '', '', '2016-02-10 10:32:43', '2016-02-10 04:32:43', '', 72, 'http://localhost/travelguide/index.php/2016/02/10/72-revision-v1/', 0, 'revision', '', 0),
