(251, 1, '2016-02-10 21:22:42', '2016-02-10 15:22:42', '<h2><span style="color: #000080;"><strong>Panam Nagar</strong></span></h2>\r\n<p style="text-align: justify;"><span style="color: #993300;"><strong><img class="wp-image-246 alignleft" src="http://localhost/travelguide/wp-content/uploads/2016/02/70174788-300x225.jpg" alt="70174788" width="169" height="127" />Panam City</strong> </span>was established in the late 19th century. It was the most important trading center of cotton fabrics during British period. Today this area is protected under the department of archaeology of Bangladesh. The city area was linked with the main city area by three brick bridges – Panam Bridge, Dalalpur Bridge and PanamNagar Bridge. It is seemed Hindu talukdars (rich businessman) select the place as their residence town. Panam Nagar, the elegant structures was rising in the last quarter of the 13th century. No need of any ticket require to visit this old town. The city gradually lost its commercial importance. Sonargaon Folk Art Museum is very near to Panam City.</p>\r\n<p style="text-align: justify;">It is about 2.5 kilometers to the north of Dhaka-Chittagong Highway at Mograpara Point. It is only 0.5km away from Sonargaon Folk Art Museum.The place is 38.4 km from Dhaka.  It is located at Sonargaon Upazila in Narayanganj district, Bangladesh. Buses are available from Gulistan. Journey will be easy if it is used Mayor Mohammad Hanif Flyover. Buses are go Gulistan, Jatrabari, Dhaka Chittagong highway. It is less the one hour journey from Dhaka and bus fare is within tk.50/- per person. It is better to go there on micro car with a group.</p>\r\n\r\n<h2><span style="color: #000080;"><strong>Loknath Brahmachari Ashram\r\n</strong></span></h2>\r\n<span style="color: #800000;"><strong><img class="wp-image-248 alignleft" src="http://localhost/travelguide/wp-content/uploads/2016/02/lokenath-baba-samadhi-300x225.jpg" alt="lokenath-baba-samadhi" width="169" height="127" />Loknath Ashram </strong></span>is based on <span style="color: #800000;"><strong>Baba Loknath (লোকনাথ ব্রহ্মচারী)</strong></span> , a saint and Hindu religion spiritual philosopher in Bengal. The Asrom is in Baradi Sonargaon Upazila in Narayanganj District under Dhaka Division.\r\n\r\nThe <em>temple</em> is 35 kilometers from Dhaka. There is a guest house, Durga mondop and pond in the ashram area. Samadhi of Baba is in this temple.The place is also very near to Joyti Basus paternal house. It is holy place for Bengali Hindu pilgrimages\r\n\r\n<span style="color: #800000;"><strong>How to Go Loknath Ashram Barodi</strong></span>\r\n<ul>\r\n	<li><span style="color: #000000;"><em>Bus is available from Gulisthan, Dhaka</em></span></li>\r\n	<li><span style="color: #000000;"><em>Normally it take 1:30 hour from Dhaka</em></span></li>\r\n	<li><span style="color: #000000;"><em>Barodi is on the to Dhaka Chittagong high way</em></span></li>\r\n	<li><span style="color: #000000;"><em>It is after Kachpur Bridge</em></span></li>\r\n	<li><span style="color: #000000;"><em>It is 35 Km from Dhaka</em></span></li>\r\n	<li><span style="color: #000000;"><em>Bus is available day and night after 30 mutinies gap</em></span></li>\r\n	<li><span style="color: #000000;"><em>Nearest bus stop is Morapara</em></span></li>\r\n</ul>\r\n&nbsp;\r\n\r\n&nbsp;\r\n\r\n&nbsp;', 'Narayanganj District', '', 'inherit', 'closed', 'closed', '', '242-revision-v1', '', '', '2016-02-10 21:22:42', '2016-02-10 15:22:42', '', 242, 'http://localhost/travelguide/index.php/2016/02/10/242-revision-v1/', 0, 'revision', '', 0),
