egion, which could be mentioned in name- Dao Bari, House of Tokani Pal, House of Choron Poddar, Old House of Makahati, House of Kamini Pal etc. It is being assumed that those palace like houses erected in contemporary time period. The owners of those palaces were mainly merchant.</p>\r\n<p style="text-align: justify;"><span style="color: #800000;"><strong>How to Go There: </strong></span></p>\r\n<p style="text-align: justify;">From Muktarpur Bus stop of Munshiganj, there are a couple of ways to move toward Mondol Bari at Abdullahpur village of Tongibari Upazila. It’s almost 7km south-west from the bridge. You may ride on a Rickshaw or Auto-rickshaw to reach there.</p>\r\n\r\n<h2><span style="color: #000080;"><strong>Ghoshal Bari Radha Krishna Temple</strong></span></h2>\r\n<p style="text-align: justify;"><img class="wp-image-274 alignleft" src="http://localhost/travelguide/wp-content/uploads/2016/02/index-2.jpg" alt="index" width="168" height="98" />About 100 years old (now rebuilt) Radha-Krisna temple with its outstanding view standing at Atpara village. The temple is situated at Atpara under Vajrayoguni Union Parisad of Munshiganj district by the road side leading to Tangibari at a distance of 7.2 km from Munshiganj town. Adjacent to this temple there are two more temples which appear to have been erected recently. It is a ‘Pancha ratna’ temple resting on a square sanctum.</p>\r\n<p style="text-align: justify;"><span style="color: #800000;"><strong>How To Go There:</strong></span></p>\r\n<p style="text-align: justify;">It’s very easy to get there at the temple from Tongibari Upazila and Munshiganj Sadar. There are significant numbers of vehicles moving through the village Atpara.</p>\r\n\r\n<h2><span style="color: #000080;"><strong>Mridha Bari</strong></span></h2>\r\n<img class="wp-image-276 alignleft" src="http://localhost/travelguide/wp-content/uploads/2016/02/index-3.jpg" alt="index" width="168" height="126" />On the way from Dhaka to Baligaon, there is a bus stand named Bejgaon. In bejgaon area, a lot of traditional house is seen. At the end of the bejgaon road, there is a house made by a local family known as Mridha Bari at the bank of Padma River. Though it is a private property, it is sometimes open for the public to pay a visit and spend some time. It is actually a Garden House surrounded by flowers.\r\n\r\n&nbsp;\r\n\r\n<span style="color: #800000;"><strong>How To Go There:</strong></span>\r\n\r\nOn the way from Dhaka to Baligaon, there is a bus stand named Bejgaon. At the end of the bejgaon road, there is a house made by a local family known as Mridha Bari at the bank of Padma River.\r\n\r\n&nbsp;\r\n<h2><span style="color: #000080;"><strong>Mirkadim Bridge</strong></span></h2>\r\n<img class="wp-image-278 alignleft" src="http://localhost/travelguide/wp-content/uploads/2016/02/images-1.jpg" alt="images" width="169" height="117" />Mirkadim bridge spans the Mir Kadim canal (creek) which runs from Mir Kadim to Tangibari. It connects the village Abdullahpur and Panam area of Rampal Union Parishad under Munshigonj District. It is situated at a distance of about 5.50 km from the district headquarters. The local tradition claims it to have been built by King Ballal Sen, but the architectural features belie the local tradition. The bridge can architecturally be attributed to the Mughal period, not earlier than 17th century.\r\n\r\n<span style="color: #800000;"><strong>How To Go There:</strong></span>\r\n\r\nIt is situated at a distance of about 5.50 km from the Munshiganj district headquarters. If anybody wants to go there,they can hire a Rickshaw or Auto-Rickshaw to reach at this bridge from the Sadar Upazila.', 'Munshiganj District', '', 'inherit', 'closed', 'closed', '', '267-revision-v1', '', '', '2016-02-10 23:19:00', '2016-02-10 17:19:00', '', 267, 'http://localhost/travelguide/index.php/2016/02/10/267-revision-v1/', 0, 'revision', '', 0);
