(282, 1, '2016-02-10 23:25:11', '2016-02-10 17:25:11', '<h2><span style="color: #000080;"><strong>Arial Khan River</strong></span></h2>\r\n<p style="text-align: justify;"><img class="wp-image-286 alignleft" src="http://localhost/travelguide/wp-content/uploads/2016/02/index-4.jpg" alt="index" width="168" height="126" />It is located in the main town of Madaripur District. Most of the major districts are established around a river. Madaripur is not alike from those. This simple but beautiful district is found around the river “Arial Khan”. Both of the banks are slapped by the almost overflowing water from the river. This river meandered the district all around and where ever you visit the district, you’ll find the river or a branch of the river.</p>\r\n<p style="text-align: justify;"><strong><span style="color: #800000;">How To Go There:</span>                  </strong></p>\r\n<p style="text-align: justify;">Dhaka to Madaripur distance is 426 Km and need 8 hours 5 minutes to reach Madaripur. There are available bus 24 hours a day. To go Madaripur Start journey from Dhaka to Mawa Ghat. BRTC, Procesta, Elish, Gungun, Ajmeri bus service are available Dhaka to Mawa Ghat. BRTC bus terminal is Gulistan and fair is 70/-, Procesta bus terminal are Uttora &amp; Rampur and fair 100/-,Elish, Gungun, Ajmari bus terminal is Jatrabari and fair is 80/-. Hire a rickshaw van of take a ride. It cost 30 taka for a rickshaw.  They can also use CNG to explore the Madaripur.</p>\r\n\r\n<h2><span style="color: #000080;"><strong>Jhaudi Giri</strong></span></h2>\r\n<p style="text-align: justify;"><strong><span style="color: #800000;"><img class="wp-image-287 alignleft" src="http://localhost/travelguide/wp-content/uploads/2016/02/images-2-300x141.jpg" alt="images" width="162" height="76" />Jhaudi Giri</span> </strong>is located in Jhaudi village of Madaripur Sadar Upazila. It’s actually a far away from the town, will take around 40 minutes to reach the place. It’s actually a large pillar made from brick. People used to say it was made by the Mog (a tribe from Bangladesh). It’s unsure why they built this large mound. But people says they made for prayer. It was much taller before, but day by day it’s decreasing in size.</p>\r\n<p style="text-align: justify;"><span style="color: #800000;"><strong>How To Go There:</strong></span></p>\r\n<p style="text-align: justify;">One can start his journey for the monument from Madaripur town any kind of motorized vehicle. We suggest travelers to hire a rickshaw van of take a ride. It cost me for 30 taka for a rickshaw.  They can also use CNG to explore the Madaripur.</p>\r\n&nbsp;\r\n<h1><span style="color: #000080;">Kalikhola Zamindar Bari</span></h1>\r\n<p style="text-align: justify;"><strong><img class="wp-image-288 alignleft" src="http://localhost/travelguide/wp-content/uploads/2016/02/index1.jpg" alt="index1" width="170" height="109" /></strong>This is locally named as “Shaha Bari”, built by someone rich merchant. The owner of the house left the house during the war 1971 with Pakistan. Before leaving the country, he somehow able to sell his properties.</p>\r\n<p style="text-align: justify;">After a few minutes of walking distance from the “Shaha Bari”, there is another old house, and this one is much larger. Actually this is the mansion of the local Zamindar of here. This house is currently occupied by the local “Land Survey” section of Madaripur. 4/5 government employees used to work here. Also the old house is using by the families of these employees. From my observation, this building is not that much older compare to other Palaces from Bangladesh. But still this place is worth to visit.</p>\r\n<span style="color: #800000;"><strong>How To Go There:</strong></span>\r\n<p style="text-align: justify;">This place is located in Kalkini Upazila of Madaripur District. Referred to how to go to Madaripur from Dhaka. One can start his journey for the monument from Madaripur town any kind of motorized vehicle. We suggest travelers to hire a rickshaw van of take a ride. They can also use CNG to explore the Madaripur.</p>\r\n<p style="text-align: justify;"></p>\r\n\r\n<h1><span style="color: #000080;">Raja Ram Temple</span></h1>\r\n<p style="text-align: justify;"><img class="wp-image-291 alignleft" src="http://localhost/travelguide/wp-content/uploads/2016/02/index3.jpg" alt="index3" width="170" height="115" />The great “Rajaram Mandir” which is located at the Khalia village from Tekerhat, Madaripur. If you are from Dhaka, then Tekerhat will be before the Madaripur town. Or if you are Madaripur, then it will be beside the Dhaka highway. Tekerhat is a landmark from Madaripur, actually this is under the Rajoir Upazila. Also for your information, the temple is near the “Peace Center” of Khalia. If you find it’s hard to locate the temple, then just ask people nearby about the Old Temple around. They can show you the path.</p>\r\n<p style="text-align: justify;"><span style="color: #800000;"><strong>How To Go There:</strong></span></p>\r\n<p style="text-align: justify;">Referred to how to go to Madaripur from Dhaka. One can start his journey for the monument from Madaripur town any kind of motorized vehicle. We suggest travelers to hire a rickshaw van of take a ride. They can also use CNG to explore the Madaripur. From the Tekerhat bus stoppage, its only 5 taka rickshaw fair.</p>\r\n<p style="text-align: justify;"></p>', 'Madaripur District', '', 'publish', 'closed', 'closed', '', 'madaripur-district', '', '', '2016-02-10 23:48:38', '2016-02-10 17:48:38', '', 0, 'http://localhost/travelguide/?page_id=282', 0, 'page', '', 0),
