 resist the temptation of having a look at the captivating old palace when they pass through the area. There is a temple just adjacent to this old palace named ‘<span style="color: #800000;"><strong>Nava-Ratna Temple</strong></span>‘ . For the readers concern, it is to inform that there are very few ‘Nava-Ratna’ Temples in Bengal.</p>\r\n<p style="text-align: justify;"><span style="color: #800000;"><strong>How To Go There:</strong></span></p>\r\n<p style="text-align: justify;">First you have to come at Aricha Ferry ghat . A BRTC bus from Gulistan used to come at Aricha Ghat. Bus fare is near about 70 taka. It will require around 2.5 hours to 3 hours to come at Aricha.</p>\r\n<p style="text-align: justify;">From the ferry ghat, you can take a rickshaw for 20 taka or auto for 10 taka to reach at the Zamindar Bari of Teota. It will take around 15 minutes to reach.</p>\r\n<p style="text-align: justify;"></p>\r\n<strong> </strong>\r\n<p style="text-align: justify;"></p>', 'Manikganj District', '', 'inherit', 'closed', 'closed', '', '306-revision-v1', '', '', '2016-02-11 12:28:13', '2016-02-11 06:28:13', '', 306, 'http://localhost/travelguide/index.php/2016/02/11/306-revision-v1/', 0, 'revision', '', 0),
