(369, 1, '2016-02-11 14:18:37', '2016-02-11 08:18:37', '<h2><span style="color: #000080;"><strong> </strong><strong>Jorbangla Temple</strong></span></h2>\r\n<p style="text-align: justify;"><img class="size-full wp-image-373 alignleft" src="http://localhost/travelguide/wp-content/uploads/2016/02/index7.jpg" alt="index7" width="237" height="213" />Jor-bangla, also called char-chala or yorubangala, is a style of temple architecture that arose in Bengal. The style involves two structures that resemble the traditional village huts of the region, one that serves as a porch, in front of the other that serves as a shrine.</p>\r\n<p style="text-align: justify;"><span style="color: #800000;"><strong>How To Go There:</strong></span></p>\r\n<p style="text-align: justify;">It is 10 kilometer away from Baliakandi Town. You can go there by taking bus.</p>\r\n\r\n<h3 style="text-align: justify;"><span style="color: #000080;"><strong>Rajbari Other Tourist Spot and Attraction:</strong></span></h3>\r\n<ul style="list-style-type: square;">\r\n	<li style="text-align: justify;"><span style="color: #008000;"><em>Mir Mosharrof Hosen Smriti Kendra</em></span></li>\r\n	<li style="text-align: justify;"><span style="color: #008000;"><em>Shah Paloan Majhar</em></span></li>\r\n</ul>\r\n&nbsp;', 'Rajbari District', '', 'publish', 'closed', 'closed', '', 'rajbari-district', '', '', '2016-02-11 14:27:14', '2016-02-11 08:27:14', '', 0, 'http://localhost/travelguide/?page_id=369', 0, 'page', '', 0),
