(390, 1, '2016-02-11 19:41:35', '2016-02-11 13:41:35', '<h2><span style="color: #000080;"><strong>Khulna Museum</strong></span></h2>\r\n<p style="text-align: justify;"><strong><img class="size-full wp-image-394 alignleft" src="http://localhost/travelguide/wp-content/uploads/2016/02/index1-4.jpg" alt="index1" width="294" height="171" /><span style="color: #800000;">Khulna Museum</span></strong> is the Divisional Museum in Khulna, situated in the Shibbari Mor/KDA Avenue area at Khulna City. Established by the department of Archaeology in 1998, this museum mainly shows the different earthen and pottery samples. However, there is a gallery to display the mythological characters of Hinduism made by Black Basalt. Additionally, on the way of entrance, there is a photo gallery too to let people aware about the historical structures of Khulna Division. Some terracotta, toys made with clay and building tiles are also there to display.</p>\r\n<p style="text-align: justify;"><strong><span style="color: #800000;">Ticket:</span> </strong>All Bangladeshi citizens can get entry by paying 20 taka. For foreigners, it is 100 taka.</p>\r\n<p style="text-align: justify;"><strong><span style="color: #800000;">Time Table:</span> </strong>During Winter it is Open from 9 Am to 5 Pm. In the summertime the timetable is from 10 Am to 6 Pm. Lunch brake is from 1 pm to 1:30 Pm. Sunday Closed<strong>.</strong></p>\r\n<p style="text-align: justify;"><span style="color: #800000;"><strong>How To Go There:</strong></span></p>\r\n\r\n<ul style="list-style-type: square;">\r\n	<li><em><span style="color: #003300;">Khulna District is connected by road, river and water.</span></em></li>\r\n	<li><em><span style="color: #003300;">From anywhere of Bangladesh, Shibbari is easy to reach by bus.</span></em></li>\r\n</ul>\r\n<h2><span style="color: #000080;"><strong>Rabindranath Complex</strong></span></h2>\r\n<p style="text-align: justify;"><strong><span style="color: #800000;"><img class="size-full wp-image-397 alignleft" src="http://localhost/travelguide/wp-content/uploads/2016/02/index-10.jpg" alt="index" width="274" height="184" />Rabindranath Complex</span></strong>, house of Bishwa kabi (poet of the universe) Rabindranath Tagore, established at Fultala Upazila under Khulna district. The name of his wife was Mrinalini.</p>\r\n<p style="text-align: justify;"><span style="color: #800000;"><strong>How To Go There:</strong></span></p>\r\n<p style="text-align: justify;">Rabindranath Complex is 36.9 km away from Khulna and 46.9 km away from Jessore. Cycle-rickshaws are the main method of transport. From the bus stand to the center or from one end of town to the other shouldn’t run more than about Tk 10, and as little as Tk4 for shorter journeys.</p>\r\n<p style="text-align: justify;"></p>\r\n<p style="text-align: justify;"></p>\r\n<p style="text-align: justify;"></p>\r\n<strong> </strong>', 'Khulna District', '', 'publish', 'closed', 'closed', '', 'khulna-district', '', '', '2016-02-11 19:55:33', '2016-02-11 13:55:33', '', 0, 'http://localhost/travelguide/?page_id=390', 0, 'page', '', 0),
