(445, 1, '2016-02-11 20:48:50', '2016-02-11 14:48:50', '<h2 style="text-align: justify;"><span style="color: #000080;"><strong>Mazar of Bulu Dewan</strong></span></h2>\r\n<p style="text-align: justify;"><span style="color: #993300;"><strong><img class="size-full wp-image-441 alignleft" src="http://localhost/travelguide/wp-content/uploads/2016/02/1-2.jpg" alt="1" width="240" height="160" />Mazar of Bulu Dewan</strong></span> is located in Boro bazar of Kaliganj Upazila of Jhenaidah district. Bulu Deouan er Mazar is another remarkable place in Kaliganj Upazila.</p>\r\n<p style="text-align: justify;"><span style="color: #800000;"><strong>How To Go There:</strong></span>\r\nIt is 19.6 km away from Jhenaidaha. For directions from Jhenaidah to Kaliganj. After reaching at Jhenaidah District, take local buses to go Kaliganj Upazila.</p>\r\n\r\n<h2 style="text-align: justify;"></h2>\r\n<h2 style="text-align: justify;"><span style="color: #000080;">Gunjanath Temple</span></h2>\r\n<p style="text-align: justify;"><span style="color: #993300;"><strong><img class="size-full wp-image-442 alignleft" src="http://localhost/travelguide/wp-content/uploads/2016/02/2-1.jpg" alt="2" width="240" height="180" />Gunjanath Temple</strong></span> is located in Boro bazar of Kaliganj Upazila of Jhenaidah district. The Gunjanath temple was built in 17th century by the then King in Kaliganj Upazila. There are other old temples in that locality. This place can be reached from Naldanga also.</p>\r\n<p style="text-align: justify;"><span style="color: #800000;"><strong>How To Go There:</strong></span></p>\r\n<p style="text-align: justify;">It is 19.6 km away from Jhenaidah.</p>\r\n\r\n<h2 style="text-align: justify;"></h2>\r\n<h2 style="text-align: justify;"><span style="color: #000080;">Cheragdani Mosque and Dighi</span></h2>\r\n<p style="text-align: justify;"><span style="color: #993300;"><strong><img class="size-full wp-image-443 alignleft" src="http://localhost/travelguide/wp-content/uploads/2016/02/3-3.jpg" alt="3" width="240" height="160" />Cheragdani Mosque and Dighi</strong> </span>are located in Jhenaidah district of Khulna division; the Dighi is also known as Dhol Somudro. The design and decoration of Cheragdani Mosque are very ancient and also the Dighi. But it looks very nice, as the interior decoration is pretty decent. By seeing the handwork on the wall, it is likely to impress a tourist. Most people in the area pray here. In Friday, the Mosque Committee do not accommodate all people.</p>\r\n<p style="text-align: justify;">There is natural beauty close to the mosque. Its made more alluring by the presence of bird and trees.. The place where the Muslims say their prayer is a huge place with nice decoration. The cut of stones made it even more elegant. This place is surrounded by trees and garden. The fragrance provides a different feeling. There are so many books here that can tell you about all the secrets about the world.</p>\r\n<p style="text-align: justify;">There is a Dighi known as Cheragdani dighi. A very big Dighi consisting of some crocodiles in the big dighi. They come near the people call them and give them something to eat.</p>\r\n<p style="text-align: justify;"><span style="color: #800000;"><strong>How To Go There:</strong></span></p>\r\n<p style="text-align: justify;">The transportation medium in the town is Rickshaw or van. Rickshaws and van can be found at ease. After reaching Jhenaidaha, a person can head there by Van or rickshaw.</p>\r\n\r\n<h2 style="text-align: justify;"><span style="color: #000080;">Bishwabat</span></h2>\r\n<p style="text-align: justify;"><span style="color: #993300;"><strong><img class="size-medium wp-image-444 alignleft" src="http://localhost/travelguide/wp-content/uploads/2016/02/4-1-300x150.jpg" alt="4" width="300" height="150" />Bishwabat (The Great Banyan)</strong></span> is located in northwestern side of Bethuli village of Kaliganj Upazila of Jhenaidah district. It was known as Mallikpur (Suitala) banyan tree. As it is huge in size so people call it Bishwabat. No other banyan tree in Asia is as large as it. Located on bank side of river the breeze makes it more elegant to watch. The original tree was involved in generation of 45 smaller trees slowly, it covers a range of 2.33 hectares. The original tree is no longer prevalent. Among aerial roots of it, 345 have penetrated the ground and 38 are still hanging. Many believe that tree grew 200-250 years ago on the wall of a local potter’s well.</p>\r\n<p style="text-align: justify;"><span style="color: #800000;"><strong>How To Go There:</strong></span></p>\r\n<p style="text-align: justify;">Jhenaidah is approximately 210km away from Dhaka. There are no rail or boat services available. After reaching at Jhenaidah, take local transport to visit that place.</p>\r\n\r\n<h2 style="text-align: justify;"><strong><span style="color: #000080;">Jhenaidah Other Tourist Spot and Attraction:</span>\r\n</strong></h2>\r\n<ol>\r\n	<li style="text-align: justify;"><span style="color: #003300;"><em>K.P. Basu’s House</em></span></li>\r\n	<li style="text-align: justify;"><span style="color: #003300;"><em>Golakata Mosque</em></span></li>\r\n	<li style="text-align: justify;"><span style="color: #003300;"><em>Noldanga Temple</em></span></li>\r\n</ol>', 'Jhenaidah District', '', 'inherit', 'closed', 'closed', '', '436-revision-v1', '', '', '2016-02-11 20:48:50', '2016-02-11 14:48:50', '', 436, 'http://localhost/travelguide/index.php/2016/02/11/436-revision-v1/', 0, 'revision', '', 0),
(446, 1, '2016-02-11 20:50:27', '2016-02-11 14:50:27', '<h2><span style="color: #000080;"><strong>Niribili Picnic Spot</strong></span></h2>\r\n<p style="text-align: justify;"><strong><img class="size-full wp-image-450 alignleft" src="http://localhost/travelguide/wp-content/uploads/2016/02/1-3.jpg" alt="1" width="259" height="194" /></strong>Niribili Picnic Spot is one of the most beautiful places in South Bengal. Surrounded by thousands of birds, attractive flower gardens, mini zoo, scenic ponds, Rural folk traditions ceremony emerged nearly this picnic spot. This Picnic spot is always filled and entertainment throughout the year, Today, approximately 50 years ago, the area was enclosed by forest.</p>\r\n<p style="text-align: justify;"><span style="color: #800000;"><strong>How To Go There:</strong></span></p>\r\n<p style="text-align: justify;">This picnic spot is 27.8 km away from Narail Town. You may go there by bus or CNG or auto rickshaw.</p>\r\n\r\n<h2 style="text-align: justify;"><span style="color: #000080;"><strong>Narail Other Touring spot and attraction:</strong></span></h2>\r\n<ol>\r\n	<li style="text-align: justify;"><span style="color: #003300;"><em>Arunima Eco Park</em></span></li>\r\n	<li style="text-align: justify;"><span style="color: #003300;"><em>Arunima Countryside and Golf Club</em></span></li>\r\n</ol>\r\n&nbsp;', 'Narail District', '', 'publish', 'closed', 'closed', '', 'narail-district', '', '', '2016-02-11 20:55:31', '2016-02-11 14:55:31', '', 0, 'http://localhost/travelguide/?page_id=446', 0, 'page', '', 0),
