(542, 1, '2016-02-12 00:04:52', '2016-02-11 18:04:52', '<h2 style="text-align: justify;"><span style="color: #000080;">Tourist Spots and Attractions Jamalpur Bangladesh</span></h2>\r\n<p style="text-align: justify;"><span style="color: #800000;"><strong>Jamalpur</strong> </span>is a district under Dhaka Division, Bangladesh. It startsas a district  on 26 December 1978.The town is located on the bank of Brahmaputra River.</p>\r\n\r\n<div class="entry-content">\r\n<div dir="ltr">\r\n<p style="text-align: justify;">The city is connected by road, rail, and river with Dhaka and the rest of the country. It has a railway big junction. There is an Asian Biggest Fertilizer Factory at Sharishabari and a sugarcane factory at Dewangonj upazila.The district consists of 7 Upazilas, 6 municipalities, 68 Union Parishads, 57 Wards, 224 Mahallas and 1532 villages.</p>\r\n\r\n<div style="text-align: justify;"></div>\r\n<div style="text-align: justify;"><span style="color: #800000;"><b>List of Top Famous Tourist Spots / Places / Attractions for Visitors</b></span></div>\r\n<ul style="list-style-type: square;">\r\n	<li style="text-align: justify;"><span style="color: #000000;"><em>Agricultural Research Center</em></span></li>\r\n	<li style="text-align: justify;"><span style="color: #000000;"><em>Dayamayi Temple</em></span></li>\r\n	<li style="text-align: justify;"><span style="color: #000000;"><em>Five domed Raspal Jame Mosque at Sarishabari (nineteenth century)</em></span></li>\r\n	<li style="text-align: justify;"><span style="color: #000000;"><em>Garo hills (Bakshiganj Upazila)</em></span></li>\r\n	<li style="text-align: justify;"><span style="color: #000000;"><em>Harish Chandra Dighi at Chandra (Jamalpur Sadar Upazila)</em></span></li>\r\n	<li style="text-align: justify;"><span style="color: #000000;"><em>Hazrat Shah Jamal Mazar</em></span></li>\r\n	<li style="text-align: justify;"><span style="color: #000000;"><em>Jamuna Fertilizer Company</em></span></li>\r\n	<li style="text-align: justify;"><span style="color: #000000;"><em>Jhil Bangla Sugar Mill</em></span></li>\r\n	<li style="text-align: justify;"><span style="color: #000000;"><em>Kendua Kalibari Mandir</em></span></li>\r\n	<li style="text-align: justify;"><span style="color: #000000;"><em>Lauchapara Paharica Amusement Park</em></span></li>\r\n	<li style="text-align: justify;"><span style="color: #000000;"><em>Narapara Fort at Sarishabari Upazila (sixteenth century)</em></span></li>\r\n	<li style="text-align: justify;"><span style="color: #000000;"><em>Kuthibari of Pradyut Thakur (Islampur Upazila)</em></span></li>\r\n	<li style="text-align: justify;"><span style="color: #000000;"><em>Neelkuthi at village Tartapara (nearly reined, in Madarganj Upazila)</em></span></li>\r\n	<li style="text-align: justify;"><span style="color: #000000;"><em>Pingna Madrasa in Sarishabari (Emperor Shahjahan’s period)</em></span></li>\r\n	<li style="text-align: justify;"><span style="color: #000000;"><em>Radhanath Jeu Mandir</em></span></li>\r\n	<li style="text-align: justify;"><span style="color: #000000;"><em>Revenue office and Dighi of the Zamindar at Fulkocha and Mahiramkul (Melandaha Upazila)</em></span></li>\r\n	<li style="text-align: justify;"><span style="color: #000000;"><em>Ranipukur Dighi at Sreepur</em></span></li>\r\n	<li style="text-align: justify;"><span style="color: #000000;"><em>Sholakuri Hill at Nandina</em></span></li>\r\n	<li style="text-align: justify;"><span style="color: #000000;"><em>Tomb of Shah Kamal</em></span></li>\r\n</ul>\r\n</div>\r\n</div>\r\n&nbsp;', 'Jamalpur district', '', 'inherit', 'closed', 'closed', '', '537-revision-v1', '', '', '2016-02-12 00:04:52', '2016-02-11 18:04:52', '', 537, 'http://localhost/travelguide/index.php/2016/02/12/537-revision-v1/', 0, 'revision', '', 0),
