(567, 1, '2016-02-12 16:29:01', '2016-02-12 10:29:01', '<p style="text-align: justify;"><span style="color: #800000;"><b>Barisal</b></span> (Bengali: <span style="color: #800000;"><strong><span lang="bn" xml:lang="bn">বরিশাল বিভাগ</span></strong></span>) is one of the seven administrative<strong> divisions</strong> of <strong>Bangladesh</strong>. Located in the south-central part of the country, it has an area of 13,644.85 km<sup>2</sup> (5,268.31 sq mi), and a population of 8,147,000 at the 2011 Census (preliminary returns). It is bounded by <strong>Dhaka division</strong> on the north, the <strong>Bay of Bengal</strong> on the south, <strong>Chittagong division</strong> on the east and <strong>Khulna division</strong> on the west. The administrative capital, <strong>Barisal</strong> city, lies in the <strong>Ganges (Padma)</strong> River delta on an offshoot of the <strong>Arial Khan River (Kirtonkhola)</strong>. Barisal division is criss-crossed by numerous rivers that earned it the nickname ''Dhan-Nodi-Kaal, Ei tine Barisal'' (rice, river and canal built Barisal).</p>\r\n<p style="text-align: justify;">The <span style="color: #800000;"><strong>06 districts</strong></span> of <strong><span style="color: #800000;">Barisal division</span></strong> are as follow-\r\n<a href="http://localhost/travelguide/index.php/barisal-district/" target="_blank">1. Barisal District</a>\r\n2. Jhalkati\r\n3. Pirozpur\r\n4. Patuakhali\r\n<a href="http://localhost/travelguide/index.php/barguna-district/" target="_blank">5. Barguna</a>\r\n<a href="http://localhost/travelguide/index.php/bhola-district/" target="_blank">6. Bhola</a></p>', 'Barisal Division', '', 'inherit', 'closed', 'closed', '', '42-revision-v1', '', '', '2016-02-12 16:29:01', '2016-02-12 10:29:01', '', 42, 'http://localhost/travelguide/index.php/2016/02/12/42-revision-v1/', 0, 'revision', '', 0),
(568, 1, '2016-02-12 16:33:00', '2016-02-12 10:33:00', '<h2 style="text-align: justify;"><span style="color: #000080;"><strong>Rajarbag Saturia Palace</strong></span></h2>\r\n<p style="text-align: justify;"><img class="size-full wp-image-569 alignleft" src="http://localhost/travelguide/wp-content/uploads/2016/02/7-3.jpg" alt="7" width="259" height="194" />Rajapur Saturia Palace is located behind Bekutia ferry dock, nearly 3 centuries ago. Besides many ponds, flower garden, three well designed Mughal building, and a main gate is also present at this palace. It comprises of 100 acres of land. Tiger of Bengal “Sher-e-Bangla A. K. Fajlul Haque was born in this place. His father passed away when he was a boy. He completed his primary education Moktab (religious school) of palace. He used to swim in a pond, the boundary of which was made by stone. Other than childhood he passed a lot of his professional life here.</p>\r\n<p style="text-align: justify;"><span style="color: #800000;"><strong>How To Go There:</strong></span></p>\r\n<p style="text-align: justify;">From Jhalakathi town, you can easily get local transport (bus, easy bike or tempo) to reach Rajapur Saturia Palace in Jhalakathi district.</p>\r\n\r\n<h2 style="text-align: justify;"><span style="color: #000080;">Jhalokathi Others Tourist Spot and Attraction:</span></h2>\r\n<ol>\r\n	<li style="text-align: justify;"><span style="color: #003300;"><em>Jibonanda das Mothers Home</em></span></li>\r\n	<li style="text-align: justify;"><span style="color: #003300;"><em>Kirtypasha</em></span></li>\r\n</ol>', 'Jhalokathi District', '', 'publish', 'closed', 'closed', '', 'jhalokathi-district', '', '', '2016-02-13 19:53:07', '2016-02-13 13:53:07', '', 0, 'http://localhost/travelguide/?page_id=568', 0, 'page', '', 0),
