ots. Rajban Bihar Pagoda is one of them. It is a very ideal place especially for the Buddhist. It looks like a golden temple. Its scenery is wonderful and attracts everybody. Rajban Vihara is called the spiritualist principal monk. It is an internationally known Buddhist Temple, where the spiritualist principal monk Shrimath Sadhana Nanda Mohasthabir (Ban Vante) lives.</p>\r\n\r\n<h4 style="text-align: justify;"><span style="color: #800000;">How to go there:</span></h4>\r\n<p style="text-align: justify;">This tourist attraction is located in Rangamati Sadar Upazila. Rajbon Bihar is just 5 kilometer away from Rangamati town. So visitor can hire private jeep or auto rickshaw to go there.</p>\r\n\r\n<h2 style="text-align: justify;"><span style="color: #000080;">Shuvolong Waterfall</span></h2>\r\n<p style="text-align: justify;"><span style="color: #800000;"><strong>Shuvolong Waterfall</strong></span> is a beautiful waterfall in Rangamati. The only available path to reach at the waterfall is through the lake. People visit there by boat. It is a famous place with the tourists for the waterfall, high hills and the natuarl surrounding it offers. This waterfall is just before the Shubholong Bazar. So that Shuvolong is easily accessible by speed boat or motor boats from Rangamati.</p>\r\n\r\n<h4 style="text-align: justify;"><span style="color: #800000;">How to go there:</span></h4>\r\n<p style="text-align: justify;">After that you will hire engine boat from tobolchari or Reserve Bazar to go to Shuvolong Waterfall. The cost around 1000 TK. To 1500 TK.</p>\r\n\r\n<h2 style="text-align: justify;"><span style="color: #000080;"><strong>Rangamati Other Tourist Spots</strong></span></h2>\r\n<ol style="text-align: justify;">\r\n	<li><span style="color: #003300;"><em>Hanging Bridge</em></span></li>\r\n	<li><span style="color: #003300;"><em>Peda Ting Ting Island</em></span></li>\r\n	<li><span style="color: #003300;"><em>Chakma Rajbari</em></span></li>\r\n</ol>\r\n<p style="text-align: justify;"><strong> </strong></p>', 'Rangamati District', '', 'inherit', 'closed', 'closed', '', '820-revision-v1', '', '', '2016-02-17 22:09:44', '2016-02-17 16:09:44', '', 820, 'http://localhost/travelguide/?p=825', 0, 'revision', '', 0),
(826, 1, '2016-02-17 22:10:16', '2016-02-17 16:10:16', '<span style="color: #800000;"><b>Chittagong Division</b></span> (Bengali: <span style="color: #800000;"><strong><span lang="bn" xml:lang="bn">চট্টগ্রাম</span></strong></span>) is geographically the largest of the seven administrative divisions of <strong>Bangladesh</strong>. It covers the south-easternmost areas of the country, with a total area of 33,771.18 km<sup>2</sup> (13,039.13 sq mi) and a population at the 2011 census of 28,423,019.\r\n\r\nChittagong Division is home to <strong>Cox''s Bazaar</strong>, one of the world''s longest natural <strong>beaches</strong>; as well as <strong>St. Martin''s Island</strong>, Bangladesh''s sole <strong>coral reef</strong>.\r\n\r\nThe <span style="color: #800000;"><strong>11 districts</strong></span> of <strong><span style="color: #800000;">Chittagong division</span></strong> are as following-\r\n\r\n<a href="http://localhost/travelguide/?page_id=755" target="_blank">1. Chittagong District</a>\r\n<a href="http://localhost/travelguide/?page_id=820" target="_blank">2. Rangamati</a>\r\n<a href="http://localhost/travelguide/?page_id=778" target="_blank">3. Cox`s Bazar</a>\r\n<a href="http://localhost/travelguide/?page_id=814" target="_blank">4. Bandarban</a>\r\n5. Khagrachori\r\n6. Comilla\r\n<a href="http://localhost/travelguide/?page_id=763" target="_blank">7. Chandpur</a>\r\n<a href="http://localhost/travelguide/?page_id=765" target="_blank">8. Brahmanbaria</a>\r\n<a href="http://localhost/travelguide/?page_id=774" target="_blank">9. Feni</a>\r\n<a href="http://localhost/travelguide/?page_id=770" target="_blank"> 10. Noakhali</a>\r\n<a href="http://localhost/travelguide/?page_id=768" target="_blank">11. Lakshmipur</a>\r\n\r\n&nbsp;\r\n\r\n&nbsp;\r\n\r\n&nbsp;', 'Chittagong Division', '', 'inherit', 'closed', 'closed', '', '38-revision-v1', '', '', '2016-02-17 22:10:16', '2016-02-17 16:10:16', '', 38, 'http://localhost/travelguide/?p=826', 0, 'revision', '', 0);
